to make a bootable drive for windows
//this is a comment//
{
sudo woeusb --target-filesystem NTFS     
--device /home/leo/Downloads/Win10_2004_English_x64.iso  /dev/sdx


ex:
sudo woeusb --target-filesystem NTFS --device /home/leo/Downloads/Win10_2004_English_x64.iso  /dev/sde

}

to know what driver is in use
lspci -k | grep -EA3 'VGA|3D|Display'

errors:
journalctl -p err
journalctl -p err -b in this boot



