xprop
to click on a program and see info about it

readlink -f filename
gives fullpath of such file

grep "xrootgif" * -R
searches everything for this specific line, in this case, xrootgif

searches all directories, sorts them and reverses them and head i see the nop 5
du -a /home | sort -n -r | head -n 5

https://www.tecmint.com/find-top-large-directories-and-files-sizes-in-linux/

ps aux | less
prints all processes running and opens it in less

gpg --recv-keys 
this will add a key ring
